            <title>[SPARK-29072] Properly track shuffle write time with refactor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29072</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-28209&quot; title=&quot;Shuffle Storage API: Writer API and usage in BypassMergeSortShuffleWriter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-28209&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-28209&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-28570&quot; title=&quot;Shuffle Storage API: Use writer API in UnsafeShuffleWriter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-28570&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-28570&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-28571&quot; title=&quot;Shuffle storage API: Use API in SortShuffleWriter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-28571&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-28571&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we used the new shuffle writer plugin API across all the shuffle writers. However, we accidentally lost time tracking metrics for shuffle writes in the process, particularly for UnsafeShuffleWriter when writing with streams (without transferTo), as well as the SortShuffleWriter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
